<section xml:id="C10.S27">
<title>Connection Formulas</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C10.S27.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.s1">
Other solutions of (10.25.1) are <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.m1">I_{-\nu}\left(z\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.m2">K_{-\nu}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.27.1" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E1">I_{-n}\left(z\right)=I_{n}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.27.2" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E2">I_{-\nu}\left(z\right)=I_{\nu}\left(z\right)+(2/\pi)\sin\left(\nu\pi\right)K_{ \nu}\left(z\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.27.3" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E3">K_{-\nu}\left(z\right)=K_{\nu}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="10.27.4" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E4">K_{\nu}\left(z\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}\pi\frac{I_{-\nu}\left(z\right)-I_{\nu}\left (z\right)}{\sin\left(\nu\pi\right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.s4">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S27.p1.m3">\nu</Math> is an integer limiting values are taken: <Math equation-number="10.27.5" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E5">K_{n}\left(z\right)=\frac{(-1)^{n-1}}{2}\*\left(\left.\frac{\partial I_{\nu} \left(z\right)}{\partial\nu}\right|_{\nu=n}+\left.\frac{\partial I_{\nu}\left( z\right)}{\partial\nu}\right|_{\nu=-n}\right), if n=0,\pm 1,\pm 2,\ldots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S27.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C10.S27.p2.s1">
In terms of the solutions of (10.2.1),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C10.S27.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.27.6" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E6">I_{\nu}\left(z\right)=e^{\mp\nu\pi i/2}J_{\nu}\left(ze^{\pm\pi i/2}\right), if -\pi\leq\pm\operatorname{ph}z\leq\tfrac{1}{2}\pi,</Math> 
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S27.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C10.S27.p3.s1">
 <Math equation-number="10.27.7" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E7">I_{\nu}\left(z\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}e^{\mp\nu\pi i/2}\left({H^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left( ze^{\pm\pi i/2}\right)+{H^{(2)}_{\nu}}\left(ze^{\pm\pi i/2}\right)\right), if -\pi\leq\pm\operatorname{ph}z\leq\tfrac{1}{2}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C10.S27.p3.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.27.8" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E8">K_{\nu}\left(z\right)=\begin{cases}\tfrac{1}{2}\pi ie^{\nu\pi i/2}{H^{(1)}_{ \nu}}\left(ze^{\pi i/2}\right),&amp;-\pi\leq\operatorname{ph}z\leq\tfrac{1}{2}\pi, \\ -\tfrac{1}{2}\pi ie^{-\nu\pi i/2}{H^{(2)}_{\nu}}\left(ze^{-\pi i/2}\right),&amp;- \tfrac{1}{2}\pi\leq\operatorname{ph}z\leq\pi.\end{cases</Math> } <Math equation-number="10.27.9" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E9">\pi iJ_{\nu}\left(z\right)=e^{-\nu\pi i/2}K_{\nu}\left(ze^{-\pi i/2}\right)-e^ {\nu\pi i/2}K_{\nu}\left(ze^{\pi i/2}\right), if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\tfrac{1}{2}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C10.S27.p3.s3">
<Math equation-number="10.27.10" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E10">-\pi Y_{\nu}\left(z\right)=e^{-\nu\pi i/2}K_{\nu}\left(ze^{-\pi i/2}\right)+e^ {\nu\pi i/2}K_{\nu}\left(ze^{\pi i/2}\right), if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\tfrac{1}{2}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C10.S27.p3.s4">
<Math equation-number="10.27.11" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S27.E11">Y_{\nu}\left(z\right)=e^{\pm(\nu+1)\pi i/2}I_{\nu}\left(ze^{\mp\pi i/2}\right) -(2/\pi)e^{\mp\nu\pi i/2}K_{\nu}\left(ze^{\mp\pi i/2}\right), if -\tfrac{1}{2}\pi\leq\pm\operatorname{ph}z\leq\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S27.p4">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C10.S27.p4.s1">
See also §10.34.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S27.p5">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C10.S27.p5.s1">
Many properties of modified Bessel functions follow immediately from those of ordinary Bessel functions by application of (10.27.6)–(10.27.8).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</section>
